<subSubSection id="7A8743D3FFE50929FD1DF9E060D7CF61" pageId="7" pageNumber="294" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="32221058FFE50929FD1DF9E060D7CF61" blockId="7.[675,1210,1549,1694]" pageId="7" pageNumber="294">
ETYMOLOGY. — Taxon named after its very large size (greek adjective μεγας, μεγαλη) and the suffix “-acris”, common in 
<taxonomicName id="F59D6BDBFFE50929FCA5F9AC60CBCF61" box="[797,911,1602,1626]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Orthoptera</taxonomicName>
